xcolorwindow
============

A simple colored window.

Options:

    -c  Color
    -h  Height
    -t  Title
    -w  Width
    -x  X position
    -y  Y position

Some example usages:

    xcolorwindow
    Displays a black window.
    
    xcolorwindow -t "Window Title"
    Displays a black window with the title "Window Title".
    
    xcolorwindow -x 128 -y 128 -w 128 -h 128
    Displays a black window with the width and height of 128 and
    with 128 pixels from the top and left.
    
    xcolorwindow -c 16711680
    Displays a red window.    

